    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-05-29T10:32:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-05-29T10:32:00-05:00" n="411"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/495: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-29T11:00:00-04:32"
                            >May 29, 1930—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. My telegram No. 30, May 28, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d411fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> President Siles resigned last night turning over the
                    Executive power to the Cabinet. Elections for a constituent assembly to revise
                    the Constitution have been called for June 29. The assembly will be composed of
                    the usual number of Senators and Deputies making up Congress and will meet on
                    July 28th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hibbard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
